-- Portuguese 10-Year Bonds Open Higher, Snapping Two-Day Plunge
-- B y   D a v i d   G o o d m a n
-- 2013-07-04T07:03:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-04/portuguese-10-year-bonds-open-higher-snapping-two-day-plunge.html
Portuguese 10-year bonds advanced for
the first time in three days, pushing the yield on the
securities down 30 basis points, or 0.3 percentage point, to
7.16 percent as of 8:01 a.m. London time.  The rate had climbed 107 basis points in the past two days,
and touched 8.11 percent yesterday, the most since Nov. 21.  To contact the reporter on this story:
